The paper deals with image stitching, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method involves warping images to preserve perspective, which is a key aspect of the problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric transformations and image processing, which are relevant to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses weighted combination schemes and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves robotics and automation, which are relevant to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to image stitching, which involves machine learning and optimization, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
